The paper deals with information-theoretic limits of support recovery problems, which involve determining a sparse subset of variables relevant in generating observations. This topic is closely related to information theory and machine learning, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with probabilistic observation models, which suggests that it may also belong to the Signal Processing (cs.SP) and Statistics (cs.SI) sub-categories.
